### isCompressingStore() {#adabdec5aa2dd92fc3bab62458dcb1b6d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="bool llvm::VPStridedStoreSDNode::isCompressingStore () const"
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Returns true if the op does a compression to the vector before storing.

The node contiguously stores the active elements (integers or floats) in src (those with their respective bit set in writemask k) to unaligned memory at base&#95;addr.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/selectiondagnodes-h/#l02717">2717</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/selectiondagnodes-h">SelectionDAGNodes.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### isTruncatingStore() {#a460088a793f44c318224e6353f104e66}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="bool llvm::VPStridedStoreSDNode::isTruncatingStore () const"
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return true if this is a truncating store.

For integers this is the same as doing a TRUNCATE and storing the result. For floats, it is the same as doing an FP&#95;ROUND and storing the result.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/selectiondagnodes-h/#l02711">2711</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/selectiondagnodes-h">SelectionDAGNodes.h</a>.
